WEBVTT

00:57.186 --> 00:58.167
Good morning, everybody.

00:58.207 --> 01:00.410
Thank you so much for being with us today.

01:00.430 --> 01:10.000
I want to welcome all of our Sugar Creek members at the Sugar Land Campus, at the Missouri City Campus, and the Richmond Rosenberg Campus.

01:10.341 --> 01:12.683
God's doing so many great things among us.

01:13.044 --> 01:22.034
We are seeing the power of His Holy Spirit among us and working in our church to see people come to faith in Christ, and we are so grateful.

01:22.114 --> 01:22.695
to the Lord.

01:22.996 --> 01:27.507
And for all of you who are worshiping with us online, welcome to Sugar Creek today.

01:28.189 --> 01:34.123
Max Volcano is one of the great Christian writers in this century.

01:34.945 --> 01:40.178
He's an amazing guy and has an amazing insight into

01:40.258 --> 01:40.939
God's Word.

01:41.820 --> 01:54.034
He has an ability to take one of the stories that we read a thousand times and just turn it a little bit, just like you would a diamond and see fresh light and a different perspective.

01:54.554 --> 02:00.781
And all of a sudden he has opened an insight to us in that familiar story that we had never seen before.

02:02.083 --> 02:07.629
Well, Maxalcato and his wife experienced a near miss.

02:07.649 --> 02:08.370
It is called.

02:08.738 --> 02:09.319
years ago.

02:09.579 --> 02:21.757
Their daughter today is grown and she is a mom now as a family, but when she was two years of age, they had a tragedy or at least near one.

02:23.319 --> 02:25.062
It was a day that everybody was busy.

02:25.082 --> 02:30.770
They had things to do and everybody was sort of paying attention to their own stuff that day.

02:32.322 --> 02:44.755
They thought they had all the bars up to make sure that their two-year-old little girl couldn't get to the backyard, but somehow, some way, she was able to get through it and get to the outside.

02:45.937 --> 03:02.034
Inside, they were all busy, and it seemed a little quieter than usual, and somebody yelled out their daughter's name but didn't get her ply, and it yelled again, and as soon as they didn't get a reply the second time, they rushed to the back door, and sure enough, there she was,

03:02.114 --> 03:08.162
in the swimming pool, drowning, and within seconds to live.

03:09.644 --> 03:12.809
Locado wrote this as a result of that.

03:12.829 --> 03:17.816
He said, it was only a matter of seconds, and we almost lost her.

03:20.019 --> 03:22.162
The thought was numbing and convicting.

03:23.263 --> 03:28.210
It was a divine slap, a gracious knock on the head of severe mercy.

03:29.762 --> 03:39.593
And because of it, I came face to face with one of the underground's slightest agents, the agent of familiarity.

03:41.836 --> 03:47.322
It is really possible for all of us to take the familiar for granted.

03:47.342 --> 03:51.226
I mean, we're with this familiar all the time.

03:51.266 --> 03:58.194
Maybe it is an it or it's a person, but we are around this thing or this person all the time.

03:59.586 --> 04:03.172
And we can start living our life, taking the other person for granted.

04:03.213 --> 04:13.571
And it's very easy to do, to take our spouse for granted, to take our family for granted, to take our church for granted, to take God for granted.

04:15.174 --> 04:17.939
And it's that very thing I want to talk to you about today.

04:18.480 --> 04:21.906
We are in the 49th year of sugar creek.

04:22.306 --> 04:25.790
And that means next year is our 50th anniversary.

04:26.051 --> 04:31.057
I've never been in a church that celebrated a 50th anniversary before, and I'm pretty excited about it.

04:31.097 --> 04:36.403
I see the plans that are being developed, and I'm really excited about what's going to happen next year.

04:37.785 --> 04:41.089
Over the course of these 49 years, it's been one miracle after another.

04:41.570 --> 04:48.178
It's as though God's hand had just given an extra portion of grace to this church from its very start.

04:48.994 --> 04:58.243
And we're gonna get a chance to see some of those miracles and those key moments of time that this church has been through.

04:58.283 --> 05:03.728
We're certainly gonna get a chance as we celebrate the 50th anniversary to get a little taste of the history.

05:04.129 --> 05:10.375
But we really want the focus to be more on the future because we feel like God's not done with us yet.

05:10.395 --> 05:15.220
And where is he wanting to take us and what is he wanting to do in and through us?

05:15.800 --> 05:17.682
Because he's not finished with us.

05:18.306 --> 05:21.171
And there's going to be more of an emphasis on that than the other.

05:21.852 --> 05:26.640
That's really what these vision nights are about in September on all of our campuses.

05:28.002 --> 05:39.421
The point of it is to get a grasp of where we're going and why we're going that direction and what God is planning to do in and through us.

05:39.761 --> 05:40.542
It's to get a vision.

05:40.563 --> 05:42.706
That's why it's called vision night of

05:42.818 --> 05:47.227
of who we are, where we're going, what God is doing next.

05:47.627 --> 05:50.774
And that's why I'm so wanting you to be there.

05:50.794 --> 05:55.102
On your campus's vision night, it's so critical that we are here.

05:55.483 --> 05:59.451
So I'm asking you for sure, please sign up and be a part of that.

05:59.852 --> 06:02.216
Plus, I will sleep better if you'll sign up.

06:02.557 --> 06:05.202
So if you would do it, I would so much appreciate it.

06:06.274 --> 06:35.634
Now we were thinking as a teaching team as we were approaching this moment, key moment of time in our church that maybe before we started talking about that in October and beyond, more about our vision and direction, maybe what we need to do is solidify again who we are to be as a church and recommit ourselves to be the church that God

06:35.778 --> 06:37.180
wants us to be.

06:37.200 --> 06:50.861
There's a passage of Scripture in the Bible that I think really defines what church is supposed to be and who a church is supposed to be better than any other place in the New Testament and its revelations chapter 1 through 3.

06:52.404 --> 06:57.512
Revelation chapter 1 is the great unveiling of the glorified Jesus.

06:58.253 --> 06:58.994
One day,

06:59.138 --> 07:06.710
Every one of our bodies are going to die and our spirit is going to leave our body and come right into the presence of Jesus Christ.

07:08.753 --> 07:13.841
The first one we're going to see when we enter heaven is going to be Jesus.

07:13.901 --> 07:20.251
And when we see him, he's not gonna look like all the Sunday school pictures that we were seeing when we were kids.

07:20.872 --> 07:23.957
Those were just imaginations of who Jesus is.

07:24.237 --> 07:27.442
But in Revelation chapter one, he gives to us

07:27.618 --> 07:38.757
the unveiling of the glorified Jesus, majestic Jesus, the powerful Jesus, the high and lifted up Jesus Christ, son of the living God.

07:42.042 --> 07:50.937
I think anybody in the world that hears about Jesus becomes a fan of Jesus, at least the Jesus they want him to be.

07:50.957 --> 07:53.842
I notice that people have

07:54.338 --> 08:01.710
really weird definitions of who Jesus is because they sort of change the whole of Jesus to be just the Jesus they want Him to be.

08:03.012 --> 08:07.159
A lot of people are fans of Jesus, but God didn't call us to be fans.

08:07.439 --> 08:10.344
He called us to be followers of Jesus Christ.

08:10.925 --> 08:19.218
He called us to understand that He is the Son of the living God, that He is all-powerful God in flesh.

08:20.098 --> 08:25.583
and to glorify and magnify Jesus Christ and follow Him wherever He leads us.

08:29.307 --> 08:33.931
And that's what Revelation chapter one unveils for us.

08:34.572 --> 08:48.946
And then in Revelation chapter two and three, He identifies seven key churches during the first century and who they were, the strengths that they had in the weaknesses

08:50.274 --> 08:58.785
And it's through that we get a great understanding of what we're supposed to be, what God wants us to be as a church.

09:00.407 --> 09:06.615
Well, so the title of the series began to be that the church God wants us to be.

09:06.855 --> 09:15.567
But the deeper our teaching team got into the passages, we started seeing that six out of seven churches, though they knew who God wanted them to be, weren't.

09:16.848 --> 09:18.130
They went out of the direction.

09:20.098 --> 09:28.850
And when Jesus identifies that He then, for all of these churches says to them, now you choose who you will be.

09:30.172 --> 09:33.156
And if you choose wrong, I'll take my presence from you.

09:34.017 --> 09:46.674
And we came to realize that every one of us, no matter how much we understand what God wants us to be, we have to make a choice of our own free will to say, will we be that church?

09:47.746 --> 09:52.860
And it was from that we changed the title to the church we choose to be.

09:52.900 --> 10:00.120
We know what God wants us to be and will we choose to be the church God wants us to be.

10:00.762 --> 10:02.386
And that's how the title came about.

10:02.946 --> 10:08.933
The first of the churches that we encounter in Revelation chapter two was the church of Ephesus.

10:08.993 --> 10:17.742
And hey, we recognize that because of the book of Ephesians that Paul wrote was to this group of people that was in that church of Ephesus.

10:19.544 --> 10:27.593
And what we discover as we start in this passage of scripture is that Jesus sees about us what other people can't see.

10:28.534 --> 10:29.315
Notice what he says.

10:29.856 --> 10:31.858
In Revelation chapter two verse one,

10:32.354 --> 10:36.321
To the angel of the church in Ephesus, there we've got the church.

10:37.243 --> 10:37.464
Right.

10:37.904 --> 10:50.488
These are the words of Him who holds the seven stars in His right hand and walks among the seven golden lampstands.

10:50.508 --> 10:53.714
We know the Him, H-I-M, is Jesus Christ.

10:54.082 --> 10:58.008
We know the seven golden lampstands are these seven churches.

10:58.569 --> 11:04.699
And it's really appropriate that he calls a church a lampstand because Jesus said, we are the light of the world.

11:05.080 --> 11:08.545
He is the light of the world and now he has put his light in us.

11:09.727 --> 11:13.393
But the world is in darkness and we are the light of the world.

11:13.633 --> 11:16.578
Well, if we begin to act like the darkness, we can't bring light.

11:18.141 --> 11:21.426
We're not to conform to the world, we're to conform to him.

11:22.530 --> 11:30.302
And then we become that light to a darkened world, the seven lampstands.

11:31.804 --> 11:36.932
Notice also that he has seven stars in his right hand.

11:38.194 --> 11:38.875
What are the stars?

11:39.176 --> 11:40.137
Well, we didn't have to wonder.

11:40.458 --> 11:47.869
In Revelation chapter 1 verse 20, he says, the mystery of the seven stars that you saw in my right hand and of the seven golden lampstands is this.

11:48.250 --> 11:50.834
The seven stars are the messengers

11:51.810 --> 11:53.111
of the seven churches.

11:54.252 --> 12:01.179
In some commentaries, they talk about the messengers are an angel that God assigns to each church.

12:01.479 --> 12:02.500
I love the thought of that.

12:03.461 --> 12:03.862
Don't you?

12:04.142 --> 12:07.885
I love the thought that there is maybe an angel that's been assigned to us.

12:08.306 --> 12:10.888
Hey, give us a whole big group of angels.

12:12.950 --> 12:14.532
I like the idea of an angel.

12:15.293 --> 12:18.916
But most of the commentaries say, no, this has nothing to do with angels.

12:19.076 --> 12:20.978
It has to do with the pastors

12:22.114 --> 12:24.277
of those churches that are the messengers.

12:25.739 --> 12:33.090
Well, I kinda like that idea too, because they're in his right hand, means safety.

12:34.171 --> 12:37.757
It means strength because not their strength, but his strength.

12:38.257 --> 12:40.420
It means that he can guide and direct.

12:43.044 --> 12:44.707
But it also means accountability.

12:46.169 --> 12:49.874
And I gotta tell you something, the accountability that I feel in my heart

12:50.146 --> 12:55.874
in leading and being the lead pastor of this church, I feel it every day of my life.

12:57.516 --> 13:19.826
The accountability scares the fool out of me, because I know that one day I am going to stand before this Jesus Christ, and I'm going to give an account for how well I taught His Word, how well I lived His Word, how true I was to listen

13:20.514 --> 13:23.659
to what he has told me and to do it.

13:26.604 --> 13:34.637
The greatest fear of my life is to be found unfaithful.

13:37.001 --> 13:37.662
It scares me.

13:39.726 --> 13:42.450
I'm not so much scared of people as I am scared of God.

13:43.234 --> 13:44.856
and scared in a good way.

13:45.136 --> 13:47.718
There is a fear of God that is a good thing.

13:47.958 --> 13:49.240
It's a reverence of God.

13:49.520 --> 13:51.442
It is, I don't want to disappoint him.

13:54.104 --> 13:56.467
I want to be found faithful.

13:58.388 --> 14:00.691
I want to be found worthy.

14:04.454 --> 14:12.722
Part of what it means if indeed the stars are the pastors of these churches is the accountability.

14:15.010 --> 14:22.319
And notice then that he walks, Jesus walks among the seven candlesticks.

14:22.540 --> 14:23.000
Do you see it?

14:23.341 --> 14:28.688
At the end of verse one, and he walks among the seven golden lampstands.

14:30.270 --> 14:32.933
Have you ever thought about Jesus being here?

14:35.276 --> 14:43.026
Being at Richmond Rosenberg, being at Missouri City, being at Sugar Land, and walking up and down the aisles,

14:43.554 --> 14:48.742
in our church, being present here, being in sitting in that empty seat right next to you.

14:51.846 --> 14:56.373
It's the idea of the verse that he's here, that he sees what's happening.

14:56.614 --> 14:57.936
He sees our heart.

14:57.956 --> 14:59.518
He sees what's true about us.

15:01.781 --> 15:03.003
He sees what's true about me.

15:06.128 --> 15:07.109
And he is among us.

15:11.977 --> 15:12.818
He sees.

15:13.922 --> 15:17.188
about us, what other people cannot see.

15:17.889 --> 15:27.667
Proverbs 15, verse 3, the Lord is watching everywhere and keeps his eye on both the evil and the good.

15:27.928 --> 15:31.775
So what does he know about this church of Ephesus?

15:32.156 --> 15:35.602
Notice what he says in verse 2 and 3, I know your deeds.

15:35.906 --> 15:37.788
your hard work and your perseverance.

15:38.128 --> 15:45.797
I know that you cannot tolerate wicked men and that you have tested those who claim to be apostles but are not and have found them false.

15:46.037 --> 15:52.624
You have persevered and have endured hardships for my name and you have not grown weary."

15:52.644 --> 15:53.545
Man, I love this.

15:54.887 --> 15:57.950
He is saying to these people, you are hard workers.

15:58.651 --> 16:01.955
When there is some event, there is something that needs to happen.

16:01.975 --> 16:05.138
You're the first to volunteer, you're there, you're in the middle of it.

16:06.146 --> 16:11.291
You have perseverance, you face hardships and difficulties and struggles, but you stay strong with me.

16:13.253 --> 16:16.856
You have honored my word and stayed faithful to the Word of God.

16:17.417 --> 16:19.078
You can't tolerate wicked men.

16:19.118 --> 16:21.961
You've tested those who claim to be apostles, but are not.

16:21.981 --> 16:23.242
You have found them to be false.

16:23.262 --> 16:24.784
These people knew their Bible.

16:25.625 --> 16:27.607
They knew truth from lie.

16:27.907 --> 16:30.349
They knew error from right.

16:30.669 --> 16:35.474
They understood what the Bible said, and they held accountable those who taught.

16:37.410 --> 16:42.457
You better teach the word of God because we know that Bible and we hold you accountable to it.

16:43.117 --> 16:45.541
These are great things.

16:45.561 --> 16:47.703
These are great things about this church.

16:47.723 --> 16:55.113
And to be honest with you, if I were writing at a synopsis of who I think Sugar Creek Baptist Church is, it'd be these words.

16:56.054 --> 16:56.635
I mean that.

16:57.676 --> 17:05.106
I believe everything about what he has said about the Church of Ephesus thus far to be who Sugar Creek Baptist Church is to.

17:06.722 --> 17:12.512
This church is the most incredible church, the most wonderful church I have ever even heard of much less been a part of.

17:13.453 --> 17:17.780
Sometimes I feel sorry for other churches, just because they're not sugar creek.

17:17.860 --> 17:19.523
I know how dumb that sounds.

17:24.211 --> 17:26.194
Did you know that in July

17:26.690 --> 17:33.761
What had happened is we'd heard all the reports that we were going to have hurricanes coming more than frequently this year.

17:33.822 --> 17:34.763
We'd heard that.

17:34.803 --> 17:36.826
So we put a task force together.

17:36.846 --> 17:37.828
They came up with the plan.

17:37.948 --> 17:41.514
One of the parts of the plan were called the buckets of love.

17:42.776 --> 17:46.362
And we rolled that out in July and of all things we had hurricane July.

17:46.863 --> 17:51.410
We never saw that one coming because no hurricanes ever come in July, but there we are.

17:52.098 --> 17:53.861
We don't know if another hurricane is coming.

17:53.901 --> 17:54.762
We wanted to be ready.

17:54.822 --> 17:56.324
We wanted to be able to help other people.

17:56.565 --> 18:08.442
And one of the ideas was to get a bucket called the buckets of love and to fill them with this whole list of things that people who've been flooded out or people who've lost their home or been displaced need.

18:09.403 --> 18:11.466
And we presented it to the church.

18:11.547 --> 18:14.230
You know how many buckets of love we got back from this church?

18:15.212 --> 18:19.378
1,400 filled buckets.

18:19.682 --> 18:20.363
of love.

18:20.383 --> 18:29.902
We got more love than we can count right now, and we have sent most of those to Second Mile Mission Center, and they are so ecstatic.

18:30.163 --> 18:31.886
This is what they had asked us to do.

18:32.247 --> 18:36.335
We sent most of those to Second Mile Mission Center, and I'm not surprised.

18:36.656 --> 18:37.938
This is this church.

18:38.722 --> 18:45.690
When we had the pandemic, we started collecting food because people couldn't go to work and they didn't go to work, they didn't get paid and how do we eat?

18:46.210 --> 18:55.060
And so when we heard this from second mile, we put the word out, this church gave a hundred tons of food.

18:55.761 --> 18:57.543
I mean, I'm blown away by that.

18:57.583 --> 18:59.545
I've had to go back to second mile two or three times.

18:59.746 --> 19:01.608
Wait a minute, a hundred tons, are you sure?

19:01.888 --> 19:02.589
That's how much?

19:02.609 --> 19:07.154
Because they would always take the food and then they'd weigh it a hundred tons.

19:09.954 --> 19:15.001
This church, you, it's amazing what you do.

19:15.061 --> 19:17.204
It's amazing how willing you are to serve.

19:17.224 --> 19:20.728
It's amazing how much you love the Word of God and know the Bible.

19:23.312 --> 19:31.963
And the same was true about this church of Ephesus, but they had a fatal flaw.

19:33.745 --> 19:37.170
Listen to what it says in verse four.

19:37.474 --> 19:40.738
Nevertheless, anytime you read a nevertheless, it won't be good.

19:41.259 --> 19:41.940
You know that, right?

19:42.380 --> 19:48.428
Nevertheless, I have something against you because you've left your first love.

19:55.417 --> 19:58.421
You've left your first love.

20:01.004 --> 20:02.706
You read theologians who

20:02.914 --> 20:06.039
sort of study the passages and writing these commentaries.

20:06.140 --> 20:11.870
And there are many who say, well, this is talking about a love for God and a love for others.

20:11.910 --> 20:16.057
You remember the lawyer that went up to Jesus and asked him, what's the greatest of all commandments?

20:16.117 --> 20:23.570
And Jesus said to love your, Lord, your God with all your heart, soul, mind and strength and to love your neighbor as yourself.

20:27.586 --> 20:32.972
And maybe it is, maybe it is both, maybe it's just a love of God or maybe it's a love for God in our neighbor.

20:34.454 --> 20:37.938
I'm not minimizing loving our neighbor as ourself.

20:38.438 --> 20:39.640
I talk about it a lot.

20:40.761 --> 20:55.538
I talk about it a lot because the Bible talks about it a lot, but this morning, I want to set that second one aside and I would have just zero in on loving God with all your heart and soul and mind and strength.

20:57.762 --> 20:58.303
See the words?

21:00.646 --> 21:09.460
You have left your love for God.

21:12.324 --> 21:16.971
The word to leave as to left is the word to abandon, or for sake.

21:17.192 --> 21:21.498
And the good news about that is that you can't abandon something you didn't already have.

21:24.904 --> 21:26.546
So at least they already had it.

21:31.042 --> 21:33.345
There's two ways to leave something.

21:34.666 --> 21:38.831
One is simply to toss it into the trash.

21:38.932 --> 21:44.278
In my neighborhood, Trash Day is every Wednesday and Saturday.

21:44.719 --> 21:50.546
And the trash truck, I mean, you can set your clock by the trash truck at 730 at our house every single time.

21:52.548 --> 22:00.658
On Wednesday morning and Saturday morning, and we always have the trash sitting out there at the road, but we got paper and

22:00.738 --> 22:04.842
and cups and cans and plastic and whatever.

22:06.764 --> 22:08.907
We put them in the trash because we don't want them anymore.

22:11.229 --> 22:12.831
We don't have any use for them anymore.

22:12.911 --> 22:13.792
So we threw them away.

22:14.893 --> 22:18.196
One of the ways to leave something is to throw it in the trash.

22:18.837 --> 22:21.680
And I don't for a second think that's what this is.

22:23.202 --> 22:24.303
I don't think they would ever do that.

22:25.384 --> 22:27.346
But there's a second way to leave something.

22:29.922 --> 22:46.821
When I was in my first year of ministry and learning how to be a pastor and I was in a little country church, I went to a little lake nearby and somebody in the church had a rowboat and it was a rowboat.

22:46.841 --> 22:48.983
There was no engine, no little motor to it.

22:49.124 --> 22:51.186
And so I had oars in the rowboat.

22:52.988 --> 22:58.514
And I went for out fishing on that little lake and on that rowboat,

22:59.138 --> 23:05.004
And I wanted to catch a fish or two, but I didn't really want them to bother me much, because I had a lot to think through.

23:05.704 --> 23:14.012
And I really was out there to just get away and to think and to pray about how I was to pastor that church.

23:14.273 --> 23:21.359
And so luckily when I go fishing, I don't really catch very much, and I have plenty of time to think.

23:21.379 --> 23:28.306
So I'm out there on that boat, and I did catch a couple of fish, and I'm thinking, and I'm out there a couple of hours,

23:28.642 --> 23:30.645
But I forgot to put the anchor down.

23:31.546 --> 23:35.132
There was an anchor in the boat, but I didn't bother to put the anchor down.

23:37.595 --> 23:39.058
And I'm out there a couple of hours.

23:39.118 --> 23:40.320
I'm not even paying attention.

23:40.460 --> 23:42.383
And whenever I said, okay, well, I guess I'm done.

23:42.683 --> 23:43.244
I'll go to shore.

23:43.625 --> 23:44.506
Where is shore?

23:45.768 --> 23:47.130
I had so left.

23:47.811 --> 23:50.014
Where I started, I had so left.

23:50.134 --> 23:54.341
I had obviously turned around because now I am disoriented.

23:54.601 --> 23:57.906
I don't even know where the place is that I started.

23:59.362 --> 24:14.563
I had to figure it out, obviously I'm here, so I did figure it out, but I took a while because I had drifted and it happened so little at a time I didn't even notice.

24:16.065 --> 24:18.167
I think one way to leave is to drift.

24:20.431 --> 24:23.455
You don't even know it's happening, it just happens.

24:25.818 --> 24:28.882
Is it possible that you've drifted?

24:29.730 --> 24:32.254
away from God.

24:35.759 --> 24:40.766
Satan cannot steal our salvation, but he can tempt us to forget how important it is.

24:41.948 --> 24:49.099
It's possible to lose the awareness of what God saved you from and what God saved you for.

24:49.139 --> 24:53.726
It's possible to grow cold about God.

24:53.886 --> 24:59.314
It's possible that Satan could slowly replace our passion for God with our passion for

24:59.810 --> 25:00.696
anything else.

25:03.051 --> 25:04.862
I think that happened to me as a teenager.

25:05.708 --> 25:06.674
The truth is

25:07.170 --> 25:10.495
Look, I grew up in a pastor's home.

25:10.515 --> 25:12.678
I heard about Jesus when I was still in the womb.

25:13.339 --> 25:20.069
And every day afterwards, it was all Jesus, Jesus this and Jesus that in our family.

25:20.149 --> 25:22.212
It was important in our family's life.

25:22.292 --> 25:24.555
And it was important in my life too.

25:24.635 --> 25:25.857
I really cared about God.

25:25.877 --> 25:30.424
And when I came to know Christ as my Savior personally, it mattered to me.

25:30.724 --> 25:34.930
When I was a teenager, I began to realize I was sort of getting cold.

25:36.578 --> 25:44.268
And one of the problems is that the church was so small, it didn't have really a youth group and I needed a youth group.

25:44.288 --> 25:47.732
I gotta tell you, I didn't get a youth group.

25:47.892 --> 25:48.793
I needed one.

25:50.696 --> 25:54.300
It's important for teenagers to have other teenagers on fire for God.

25:54.320 --> 26:03.792
They can be around and times whenever you start sort of drifting away from God, you're with other friends that know God and love God and matter and they can help bring you back.

26:03.832 --> 26:05.394
And I didn't have that.

26:06.594 --> 26:16.899
And I saw as a teenager how cold I had drifted how far away from God.

26:16.919 --> 26:19.826
Did you know it's possible as a pastor to do the very same thing?

26:21.186 --> 26:29.201
In fact, in a pastor's life of staff person's life, there's so many things to get done.

26:29.221 --> 26:31.446
There are so many forms to fill out.

26:31.506 --> 26:33.009
There's so much accountability.

26:33.069 --> 26:35.133
There are so many things we have to do.

26:35.473 --> 26:39.241
It's possible that we're clicking them off and there is never a day.

26:39.541 --> 26:42.807
Any pastor of any kind can go home and say, I got the job done.

26:43.008 --> 26:44.210
There's no such thing.

26:47.266 --> 26:55.001
And it's possible to be so inundated with so many things that you can get so busy for God.

26:56.003 --> 26:57.466
You don't have any time for God.

26:59.389 --> 27:02.816
It's possible for pastors who experience that and anybody else.

27:04.239 --> 27:08.146
So busy for God that I don't have any time for God.

27:14.178 --> 27:14.979
We can drift.

27:15.459 --> 27:24.109
And that is why Hebrews 2.1 says, we must pay more careful attention, therefore, to what we have heard so that we don't drift away.

27:26.111 --> 27:28.854
Jesus was talking about a personal closeness with God.

27:28.894 --> 27:31.577
And my question to you is, has that happened to you?

27:33.700 --> 27:35.342
I'm not calling you a bad person.

27:35.722 --> 27:37.624
I'm not saying you don't believe in the Bible.

27:37.644 --> 27:39.626
I'm not saying you don't serve God.

27:39.867 --> 27:42.930
I am just asking in all of the activity

27:43.458 --> 27:50.311
Is it possible that you've gotten too busy for God?

27:52.755 --> 27:53.456
So what do you do?

27:54.578 --> 28:00.289
If it happens, if the drifting is taking place, however long it has been, what do you do?

28:00.509 --> 28:02.653
Well, Jesus addresses that in the passage.

28:03.074 --> 28:07.442
He says, becoming passionate about Christ again is a decision.

28:07.618 --> 28:08.379
Not an emotion.

28:08.599 --> 28:10.661
There can be emotions that come with it.

28:10.901 --> 28:14.945
Emotions are great, they're wonderful, but it's a decision, it's an act of the will.

28:17.848 --> 28:22.653
Revelation chapter two, verse five, remember the height from which you've fallen.

28:24.976 --> 28:27.278
Repent and do the things you did at first.

28:28.099 --> 28:31.722
And if you don't repent, I'll come to you and remove your lampstand from its place.

28:32.663 --> 28:35.346
There's three things that Jesus says in the passage.

28:36.386 --> 28:44.016
First of all, he says, remember, remember what it was like when you felt passionately in love with God.

28:44.036 --> 28:52.266
Has there ever been a time in your life that you were closer to God, more passionate about God in your life than you are right now?

28:53.087 --> 28:57.613
Has there ever been a time in your life that you were more on fire for God than you are right now?

28:57.933 --> 29:00.636
And if it is, it means you're backslidden.

29:02.899 --> 29:05.202
Maybe it's three days, maybe it's

29:06.114 --> 29:14.264
Three years, maybe it's 30 years, but however long it's been, has there ever been a time you were so on fire for God, he was right here with me.

29:14.584 --> 29:16.887
I love him, oh God, I do anything for you.

29:18.169 --> 29:19.410
More than you are now.

29:20.271 --> 29:24.336
He says, how you get back is you remember that time.

29:24.376 --> 29:25.698
You remember what it was like.

29:25.738 --> 29:28.702
You remember the thoughts you were having and the feelings you were having.

29:30.504 --> 29:32.526
Remember the way it was.

29:34.589 --> 29:35.410
Second of all,

29:35.586 --> 29:36.487
then change.

29:36.868 --> 29:38.010
It's the word repent.

29:38.450 --> 29:41.635
The word repent that he uses means that you're going in one direction.

29:41.655 --> 29:42.616
You realize it's wrong.

29:42.636 --> 29:43.237
It's a sin.

29:44.079 --> 29:46.162
You turn around and go the other direction.

29:48.585 --> 29:49.687
I'm going the wrong way.

29:49.847 --> 29:51.950
I'm misappropriating my time.

29:52.070 --> 29:55.676
I'm doing something other than spending time with God.

29:58.199 --> 30:00.603
Maybe Facebook's become too important to me.

30:03.467 --> 30:05.490
I'm not spending any time with God.

30:06.562 --> 30:07.703
are the time I should be.

30:07.744 --> 30:14.652
It is second of all to change, to come to a brokenness over what you have lost.

30:15.093 --> 30:17.636
Admit the truth as forgiveness.

30:17.877 --> 30:23.304
And then third is this, do the things you did when your walk with God was strong.

30:25.486 --> 30:26.307
What were you doing?

30:27.669 --> 30:31.474
One of the things that had to be was you were spending time in prayer with God.

30:34.018 --> 30:43.090
The times that we were the closest to God is the times we were having those times in prayer with God.

30:43.150 --> 30:51.501
And in those times we would tell Him how much we loved Him, how much we cared for Him, how important He was to our life.

30:51.802 --> 30:55.587
There are some times we go to prayer and we shouldn't even bring up anything.

30:55.947 --> 30:57.409
It's not wrong to pray for stuff.

30:57.429 --> 30:59.532
Yeah, the Bible tells us to pray for stuff.

31:00.413 --> 31:04.018
And it's called prayer requests and supplication and these things.

31:05.314 --> 31:10.761
Sometimes we go, and it's just to say, God, I want to tell you how much I love you.

31:12.884 --> 31:13.425
I need you.

31:13.445 --> 31:14.967
I want you.

31:17.611 --> 31:20.194
I care when you direct me.

31:20.254 --> 31:23.499
I care when you tell me I'm going the wrong direction.

31:23.619 --> 31:29.026
I want to please you, and I've just come to say, God, I love you.

31:30.668 --> 31:34.994
But a prayer life that gets to fervency

31:35.586 --> 31:37.990
of prayer is so important.

31:38.010 --> 31:52.131
The Bible says in James 516, the effective fervent prayer of a righteous man, and it means both genders, men, and women, the effective fervent prayer of a righteous person avails much.

31:54.014 --> 32:04.210
How long has it been since you cried for another person to be saved?

32:04.898 --> 32:12.329
How long has it been since there was a request that you felt so deeply for that you cried?

32:13.431 --> 32:17.677
Oh, God, please heal this person.

32:17.697 --> 32:23.846
How long has it been since you had fervency in your prayers with God?

32:26.050 --> 32:34.322
Part of what it means is that we are willing to rebuild that time with God.

32:35.554 --> 32:36.395
and the fervency.

32:37.216 --> 32:43.282
But part of that is we need to learn to hear and obey what God tells us through His Word.

32:43.863 --> 32:46.085
God speaks to us through His Word.

32:47.527 --> 32:53.213
I have come to understand the voice of God in my heart when He speaks to my heart.

32:53.473 --> 33:01.522
But there has never been a time, never will be a time that God tells me something in my heart that violates what He tells me in His Word.

33:03.042 --> 33:09.231
It will always align with it because the ultimate test is what does God say in His Word.

33:10.212 --> 33:13.717
And that's why we need to keep bringing His Word into our heart.

33:14.599 --> 33:30.642
I found myself in a situation recently in which I was pretty upset with another person, not my wife, not my wife, not a member of my family, nobody at the church

33:32.706 --> 33:37.873
but pretty upset with another person because I felt like I had been taken advantage of.

33:37.953 --> 33:45.203
And so I was praying about it and telling God how bad this person is.

33:45.363 --> 33:58.381
And he reminded me of something that he said in the book of Proverbs that applied to my situation.

34:00.104 --> 34:01.906
I didn't really like it.

34:02.306 --> 34:07.012
told him, let's don't talk about that part, but he insisted.

34:10.577 --> 34:14.502
And I had to admit, I really done this to myself.

34:17.245 --> 34:19.007
Then I wasn't upset with the guy anymore.

34:19.969 --> 34:20.750
I just let it go.

34:20.770 --> 34:26.477
And then of all things, it really turned out well.

34:29.461 --> 34:30.482
And I think

34:30.882 --> 34:40.013
Part of what was happening with all of it was about me, not the other guy.

34:40.033 --> 34:46.981
I'm telling you, the Word of God can give you direction and leadership in your life in the worst of situations in the most odd of moments.

34:49.083 --> 34:51.326
And that's why the Bible is so important.

34:51.886 --> 34:55.090
We got to keep bringing it into our heart.

34:55.394 --> 35:15.122
Chuck Colson died at the age of 81, and Chuck Colson, for those of you who are younger, unless you're just a history student, you're not going to recognize the name, but he goes back to the 1970s in which he was a mean dude, political dude, and he went to prison for the things that he did.

35:15.202 --> 35:23.474
He broke the law, he ended up in prison, and it turned out to be the greatest thing that ever happened to him, because in prison he came to know Christ as a savior.

35:24.066 --> 35:28.552
And no one would have ever thought this guy would have been a Christian.

35:28.572 --> 35:33.939
But he came to brokenness in his life and came to know Jesus Christ, his Savior's whole life was changed.

35:34.199 --> 35:39.486
And now all of us, the rest of his life dedicated to ministry is pretty amazing what he did.

35:39.786 --> 35:41.569
He wrote this book called Loving God.

35:41.649 --> 35:44.112
And here's some of the statements in the book.

35:44.132 --> 35:48.978
Loving God is a passionate desire to obey and please God.

35:49.474 --> 35:54.879
It's not just emotion, it's a desire to obey Him and please Him.

35:55.039 --> 35:58.443
It goes on to say, the key to loving God is knowing and obeying the Bible.

36:00.245 --> 36:08.433
What made me a radical Christian was not going to prison, but taking to heart the truths revealed in Scripture.

36:10.314 --> 36:18.162
And the more you do, the more you take the Word of God and let it speak, the deeper you will grow.

36:18.242 --> 36:19.063
in your love for God.

36:19.083 --> 36:25.433
And Jesus said exactly the same thing in John 14, 15, if you love me, you will obey my word.

36:27.876 --> 36:31.822
The evidence of loving God is to obey his word.

36:33.425 --> 36:38.492
One of the things that I've experienced in my life is to practice the presence of God in my life.

36:39.173 --> 36:42.258
Do you know he is actually sitting right next to you right now?

36:43.170 --> 36:45.253
He's in my car when I'm in my car.

36:45.313 --> 36:48.217
He is where I am, where I am.

36:48.758 --> 36:53.344
He is beside me all the time.

36:53.664 --> 36:58.251
And when I practice that presence, something changes about me.

36:58.551 --> 37:01.755
I sort of get myself under control.

37:02.737 --> 37:03.858
I know he's right here.

37:04.820 --> 37:12.370
I sort of be more open to hearing what he says in his word, because after all, he is right here.

37:12.642 --> 37:13.303
beside me.

37:15.285 --> 37:17.968
There's one more thing and we're done and it's simply this idea.

37:18.608 --> 37:22.232
He gives us a warning that we must not ignore.

37:23.734 --> 37:33.064
He says in verse 5 of Revelation 2, if you did not repent, I will come to you and remove your lampstand from its place.

37:34.466 --> 37:40.092
Well, I've been talking more individually, but now it's time to talk corporatively.

37:40.112 --> 37:42.354
That's, he was talking about the church.

37:45.890 --> 37:57.087
What we can't do as a church is to be so active and so involved, and yes, we believe what the Bible says, but we as a church are not close to Him.

38:00.392 --> 38:10.687
And Jesus said to the church of Ephesus, if you don't come back in your relationship with me, your personal relationship with me, I'll remove your lampstand from its place.

38:10.707 --> 38:12.610
What it simply means is I leave.

38:13.972 --> 38:15.474
I cannot think of a worse

38:15.906 --> 38:22.835
I can't think of a worse thing that could ever happen to a church than for Jesus to walk out the door.

38:24.397 --> 38:45.746
See, I am convinced there are a lot of churches meeting today and Jesus is not there because there were moments in time in that church's life in which he called them to repentance for something

38:47.458 --> 38:51.262
And they said, no.

38:51.282 --> 38:52.443
And he walked out the door.

38:54.906 --> 39:06.058
I cannot think of anything worse that could ever happen to our church and for us to be in such a way that he would walk out the door.

39:08.800 --> 39:14.066
And I'm asking us individually and us corporately as a church

39:14.978 --> 39:17.942
all our campuses and online, all of us.

39:22.648 --> 39:23.629
Go back to God.

39:26.192 --> 39:34.343
And if there has been a time in which you were closer to God than you are now, remember, change.

39:37.667 --> 39:38.388
Obey Him.

39:39.269 --> 39:40.050
Come back to Him.

39:42.753 --> 39:43.314
Let's pray.

39:43.394 --> 39:46.337
Father, we come to you today and we say, oh, God, we need you.

39:46.778 --> 39:47.739
Oh, God, we love you.

39:47.759 --> 39:48.480
We want you.

39:49.921 --> 39:54.346
And we ask that you would be Lord of us.

39:56.929 --> 40:06.319
You would be the God of this church and the God of our heart.

40:06.339 --> 40:09.202
God, would you be in the midst of our life

40:10.274 --> 40:22.103
and bring us to yielding ourselves to your word and nothing else, no outside other voices, but to hear you and yield ourself to you.

40:24.448 --> 40:28.498
And we pray this in Jesus' name, amen.

